30/10/2005
BRDO PRI KRANJU, Slovenia -- The interior ministers of 14 Central and Southeast European countries sealed a joint declaration Friday (28 October) vowing co-operation in the fight against organised crime and illegal migration and in enhancing security. 
The document was signed at the end of a regional conference. 
Addressing the forum, Austrian Interior Minister Liese Prokop vowed that security would be one of the priorities of the future Austrian presidency of the EU, which starts in the first half of next year. 
(Hina, HRT - 28/10/05)
